{
  "stem": "3097.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My mother's-- my-- this was the-- the father of my uncle's-- my grandfather's wife, this-- [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Kaminski, ?] which was the president of the-- of the Jewish Federation.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "My father's grand, grandfather used to be called Moshe [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Rofe ?].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Rofe, ?] in Hebrew, is a-- a-- a doctor, a healer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Well, I don't think he was a healer, but they used to call him like that.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And was-- those are two legends of the family that I-- that carry with me, and I knew about it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "As a child, I didn't pay too much attention to the extended family, as far as who, where, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "I knew only the uncles, and I knew my cousins, and with my parents, because I think it was different than here.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Here it's a bit different.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "In Poland, on the old country, your people used to live together in the homes and so forth.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But by us, we were a little more assimilated, you see.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Each was on his own, like, you know, one was a dentist, one was a lawyer, one was this.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was not-- a-- we didn't live in one place, and we didn't live in a village like in a shtetl.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Our town was over 80,000 people, and out of the 80,000 in 1940 were 26,000 Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we had societies there with high cultural development and possibilities.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was a little bit different.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "At the end of the war there were two Jews left in your town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One Jew was actually-- he was not a Jew.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was a [? cadera. ?] He was a converted Jew.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I think he's still alive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- the pogrom-- I escaped from there by the end of 1945.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
